  <Placemark>
    <name>Book Building</name>
    <description><![CDATA[140 East Houston, San Antonio; MARKER REPORTED MISSING 5/2011 (may be inside building)<br/><br/><b>Address:</b> 140 East Houston, San Antonio<br/><br/><b>Marker Text:</b> During the 1850s, the U.S. Army occupied several stone and adobe buildings which stood at this site. Dwight Dana Book (1869-1955), a civil engineer and veteran of the Spanish-American War, bought the property in 1904. He had this red brick commercial building erected in 1906. Attorney's, realtors, architects, physicians and other tenants leased office space here. A popular club called the "Night Spot" was once located in the basement level. (1978)]]></description>
    <Point><coordinates>-98.493369,29.426343,0</coordinates></Point>
  </Placemark>
