  <Placemark>
    <name>King's Highway - Camino Real - Old San Antonio Road</name>
    <description><![CDATA[In front of bank, SW corner of IH-410 and Nacogdoches.  Pink granite marker 83 of 128 placed in 1918.<br/><br/><b>Address:</b> 1100 NE IH-410, San Antonio<br/><br/><b>Marker Text:</b> King's Highway - Camino Real - Old San Antonio Road. Marked by the Daughters of the American Revolution and the State of Texas A. D. 1918]]></description>
